2023-04-10, **Chiral perturbative relation for neutrino masses in the type-I seesaw mechanism**, Masaki J. S. Yang et.al., [2304.04513v1](http://arxiv.org/abs/2304.04513v1)

 In this letter, we perform a perturbative analysis by the lightest singular value $m\_{D1}$ of the Dirac mass matrix $m\_{D}$ in the type-I seesaw mechanism. As a result, the mass $M\_{1}$ of the lightest right-handed neutrino $
u\_{R1}$ is expressed as $M\_{1} = m\_{D1}^{2}/ \|(m\_{
u})\_{11}\|$ by the mass matrix of the left-handed neutrinos $m\_{
u}$ in the diagonal basis of $m\_{D}$.   Since $m\_{D1} \sim 1$ MeV and $\|(m\_{
u})\_{11}\| \sim 1$ meV lead to $M\_{1} \sim 10^{6}$ GeV, such a $
u\_{R1}$ with a tiny Yukawa coupling $y\_{
u 1} \sim O(10^{-5})$ may indirectly influence observations of IceCube. On the other hand, the famous bound of the thermal leptogenesis $M\_{1} \gtrsim 10^{9}$ GeV that requires $m\_{D1} \gtrsim 30$ MeV seems to be difficult to reconcile with a simple unified theory.
